    <item>
      <title>Episode 21: Bicep with Alex Frankel</title>
      <link>https://unhandledexceptionpodcast.com/posts/0021-bicep/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 13 Aug 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://unhandledexceptionpodcast.com/posts/0021-bicep/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In this episode, I was joined by &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/adotfrank&#34;&gt;Alex Frankel&lt;/a&gt; to chat about &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/Azure/bicep&#34;&gt;Azure Bicep&lt;/a&gt;! Bicep is a new DSL that transpiles down to native ARM templates. Except that it &lt;em&gt;greatly&lt;/em&gt; improved upon the very hard to read and write ARM templates, making &lt;em&gt;Infrastructure as Code&lt;/em&gt; in Azure a far nicer user experience. We delved into the Bicep language, the tooling, a bit of the history - and even geeked out a bit on how awesome .NET has become!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
